<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-11-06T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-11-06T23:00:00-05:00" n="351" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d351">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/7349: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Lockhart</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-11-07T12:00:00+08:00">November 7,
                                1935—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received November 7—6:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>122. Embassy’s 121, November 6, 5 p.m. Chin Teh-chun, Acting Chairman of
                            Chahar, has been appointed Mayor of Peiping, and Hsiao Chen-ying has
                            been given the Chairmanship of Chahar. Both are close followers of Sung
                            Che-yuan.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to Nanking.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lockhart</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>